                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date>Second half of the 19th century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይበል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይሕ፡ for ይበል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipit of Text I and its sections;
                           titles of the books to be read; one initial word of prayers to be read;
                           prayer numbers; directives to the ministers and their abbreviation; the
                           words ʾǝgäle, ǝgälit, märʿawi and märʿat; elements of the punctuation
                           signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#4r">f. 4r: </locus>
                        <desc>Crude coloured drawing, unidentified character.</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#35r">f. 35r</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation or ownership note (?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#35r">35r</locus>: ይህ፡ መጽሃፍ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ሚካኤል፡ ቤት፡ ምካእ፡
                              ተቀባለ፡ ሃለቃ፡ ተስፋይ፡ ካሕሳይ።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Crudely written in pencil. The recent note states that the Ms. is
                              in the possession of Mikāʾel church of Bet Mǝkaʾǝ and was received
                              from (?) haläqa Tasfāy Kaḥsay (s. also Varia). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#36ra">f. 36ra</locus>
                           <desc>-rb: ʾAndǝmta-commentary on an unidentified Gǝʿǝz text,
                              incomplete.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> In Amharic with quotation in Gǝʿǝz; incomplete, starting abruptly.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- List of names (?) crudely written in pencil and hardly
                           legible: <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>.
 - Crude note written in the
                           upper margin: <locus from="18v" to="19r">18v-19r</locus> mentioning the
                           donor of the Ms.(?): አቶ፡ ሃለቃ፡ ተስፋይ፡ ቅድስት(?)፡ ካሕሳይ.
 - Written in the
                           upper margin: <locus target="#29v">29v</locus>: ስብከት.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
